  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: After sending an asset and returning back to the chat the place for keyboard does not collapse. There is an empty space below the \"Type a message\" input. It does not happen on every device though. Can be reproduced on iPhone 6 but not on a faster device like iPhone X.  \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/36907184-404713d4-1e38-11e8-8edd-6101fae5364f.png\" width=\"300\"> \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThere is no empty space. \"Type a message\" input is at the very bottom of the screen.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThere is an empty space. It fixes when user clicks on the input and keyboard appears.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Go to a chat\r\n- Click `/send`\r\n- **Expand the \"Advanced\" in Send transaction**\r\n- Sign transaction\r\n- Click \"Got it\" and return to the chat\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, March 2\r\n* Operating System: iOS 11.2.1\r\n* Device: iPhone 6\r\n* Couldn't reproduce on iPhone X or Android devices \r\n\r\n",
